thumb|frederic dannay ( left ) , with james yaffe ( 1943 )   daniel nathan , professionally known as frederic dannay ( october 20 , 1905   – september 3 , 1982 ) , and emanuel benjamin lepofsky , professionally known as manfred bennington lee ( january 11 , 1905   – april 3 , 1971 ) , were american cousins from brooklyn , new york who wrote , edited , and anthologized detective fiction under the pseudonym of ellery queen .

mysteries : 1st cousins dannay & lee wrote the ellery queen stories under this pen name

